OL,4,CTeachers 'struggle to deal with
OL,5,Cclassroom sexual abuse'
OL,6, Teachers say they do not feel equipped
OL,7, to deal with peer-on-peer sexual abuse
OL,8, because they have had no training.
OL,10,FMore than 1,500 UK teachers replied to
OL,11,Fa questionnaire from BBC Radio 4's File
OL,12,Fon 4 and teachers' union the NASUWT.
OL,14,FMore than half said they did not think
OL,15,Fadequate procedures were in place in
OL,16,Ftheir schools to deal with  abuse.
OL,18,FMany are also unsure how to deliver
OL,19,Felements of a new sex-and-relationships
OL,20,Fcurriculum, which the government says
OL,21,Fthird parties might now help with.
